@Performance_Hints
mmap(2) is O(pages) for page-table allocation but typically O(1)
amortized because NetBSD uses lazy population — pages are allocated and
PTEs installed only on first-touch. MAP_FIXED must clear any prior
mapping at the target range, adding a tear-down cost proportional to the
